      • NSDate

        public NSDate(String textRepresentation)
       throws ParseException
        Parses a date from its textual representation. That representation has the following pattern: yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ss'Z'
        Parameters:
        textRepresentation - The textual representation of the date (ISO 8601 format)
        Throws:
        ParseException - When the date could not be parsed, i.e. it does not match the expected pattern.
